summary: This is an FBI ELSUR (Electronic Surveillance) evidence envelope form documenting the chain of custody for intercepted communications. It indicates the evidence is related to a Title III court-authorized intercept and includes fields for signatures, dates, and storage details.
keyFacts: The document is an FBI ELSUR evidence envelope form used for tracking intercepted communications.
It indicates the evidence is from a Title III court-authorized intercept (not consensual monitoring).
The form includes chain of custody tracking with multiple signature fields for evidence handling.
The evidence medium appears to be a magnetic tape (ID#: 1D-6, Tape/Disk#: 4 441- _9 7).
The form is partially filled out but contains incomplete or illegible date and location information.
